  <h2>// What CAPI Stands For</h2>
  <p>
    CAPI stands for <strong>Conversions API</strong> — originally coined by Meta (Facebook) to describe their server-side event tracking endpoint, launched in 2020 as a response to Apple's iOS 14 privacy changes. The term has since expanded colloquially: "Shopify CAPI" now commonly refers to any server-side conversion tracking setup on a Shopify store, including Meta's Conversions API, Google's Enhanced Conversions, and TikTok's Events API.
  </p>

  <h2>// How Shopify CAPI Works — The Data Flow</h2>

  <div class="flow-diagram">
    <div style="font-size:10px; font-weight:700; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom:0.5rem; letter-spacing:0.1em;">// SERVER-SIDE EVENT FLOW</div>
    <div class="flow-row">
      <div class="flow-node active">CUSTOMER PURCHASES</div>
      <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
      <div class="flow-node active">SHOPIFY ORDER CREATED</div>
