    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Is CAPI the same as the Meta Pixel?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        No. The Meta Pixel is a browser-based JavaScript tag that fires from the customer's device. The Conversions API (CAPI) sends the same events from your server, bypassing the customer's browser entirely. They serve complementary roles — running both together with deduplication provides the most complete event coverage.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Does Shopify have a built-in CAPI for Meta?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Shopify's Meta Sales Channel includes a basic CAPI connection, but it requires active use of the Meta Business Suite integration and provides limited configuration control. Merchants who use a separate Meta Pixel (not via Shopify's Meta channel) need to implement CAPI independently. CAPI Shield provides full CAPI coverage independent of which Meta integration you use.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">Does CAPI work with Google as well as Meta?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        Yes. Google's equivalent of Meta CAPI is called Enhanced Conversions — it sends hashed customer data server-side to improve conversion matching in Google Ads. A complete server-side tracking setup covers both Meta CAPI and Google Enhanced Conversions. CAPI Shield by Stack Architect implements both at zero cost.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-question">How do I know if my CAPI is working correctly?<span class="chevron">▾</span></button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        In Meta Business Manager, check Events Manager → your Dataset → Test Events. Place a test order on your Shopify store and verify that a server-side Purchase event appears in the test results. The event source should show "Server" (not "Browser") for CAPI events. For Google, verify Enhanced Conversions in Google Ads → Goals → Conversions → the relevant conversion action should show "Enhanced" matching status.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

